Context: The General Arts and Science - English for Academic Purposes Program is offered at George Brown College. Online information sessions for this program are held online, webinar style, and attendees will receive a link 48 hours in advance. Interested individuals can sign up to receive updates about application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, tours, and more. The contact details provided are: 416-415-2000 for regular calls, TTY: 1-877-515-5559 for telecommunications devices for the deaf, and ask.george@georgebrown.ca for emails. The college's social media hub can also be visited for further information. It is important to note that the information on the website is subject to change without notice and should not be considered a representation, offer, or warranty. Students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
